.TEXT,SETS
837,0,Health Care Claim \058 Institutional
837,1,HC
837,2,This X12 Transaction Set contains the format and establishes the data contents of the Health Care Claim Transaction Set \040837\041 for use within the context of an Electronic Data Interchange \040EDI\041 environment\046 This transaction set can be used to submit health care claim billing information\044 encounter information\044 or both\044 from providers of health care services to payers\044 either directly or via intermediary billers and claims clearinghouses\046 It can also be used to transmit health care claims and billing payment information between payers with different payment responsibilities where coordination of benefits is required or between payers and regulatory agencies to monitor the rendering\044 billing\044 and\047or payment of health care services within a specific health care\047insurance industry segment\046 For purposes of this standard\044 providers of health care products or services may include entities such as physicians\044 hospitals and other medical facilities or suppliers\044 dentists\044 and pharmacies\044 and entities providing medical information to meet regulatory requirements\046 The payer refers to a third party entity that pays claims or administers the insurance product or benefit or both\046 For example\044 a payer may be an insurance company\044 health maintenance organization \040HMO\041\044 preferred provider organization \040PPO\041\044 government agency \040Medicare\044 Medicaid\044 Civilian Health and Medical Program of the Uniformed Services \040CHAMPUS\041\044 etc\046\041 or an entity such as a third party administrator \040TPA\041 or third party organization \040TPO\041 that may be contracted by one of those groups\046 A regulatory agency is an entity responsible\044 by law or rule\044 for administering and monitoring a statutory benefits program or a specific health care\047insurance industry segment\046 
837,4,005010X223A2\044 Health Care Claim\058 Institutional \040837\041
837~1,7,ST\042837\042987654\042005010X223A2\126
837~10,0,Loop 1000 contains submitter and receiver information\046 If any intermediary receivers change or add data in any way\044 then they add an occurrence to the loop as a form of identification\046 The added loop occurrence must be the last occurrence of the loop\046
837~10,3,Receiver Name
837~10,7,NM1\04240\0422\042XYZ RECEIVER\042\042\042\042\04246\042111222333\126
837~101,3,EPSDT Referral
837~101,4,Required on Early \038 Periodic Screening\044 Diagnosis\044 and Treatment \040EPSDT\041 claims\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~101,7,CRC\042ZZ\042Y\042ST\126
837~101~1,1,Code Qualifier
837~101~1~ZZ~1~0,0,EPSDT Screeing referral information\046
837~101~2,1,Certification Condition Code Applies Indicator
837~101~2,14,The response answers the question\058 Was an EPSDT referral given to the patient\063
837~101~2~N~1~0,0,If no\044 then choose \147NU\148 in CRC03 indicating no referral given\046
837~101~3,14,The codes for CRC03 also can be used for CRC04 through CRC05\046
837~101~3,30,Condition Indicator \0351
837~101~3~AV~1~0,0,Patient refused referral\046
837~101~3~NU~1~0,0,This conditioner indicator must be used when the submitter answers \147N\148 in CRC02\046
837~101~3~S2~1~0,0,Patient is currently under treatment for referred diagnostic or corrective health problem\046
837~101~3~ST~1~0,0,Patient is referred to another provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment for at least one health problem identified during an initial or periodic screening service \040not including dental referrals\041\046\r\nOR\r\nPatient is scheduled for another appointment with screening provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment for at least one health problem identified during an initial or periodic screening service \040not including dental referrals\041\046
837~101~4,0,Required when a second condition code is necessary\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~101~4,14,Use codes listed in CRC03\046
837~101~4,30,Condition Indicator \0352
837~101~4~AV~1~0,0,Patient refused referral\046
837~101~4~NU~1~0,0,This conditioner indicator must be used when the submitter answers \147N\148 in CRC02\046
837~101~4~S2~1~0,0,Patient is currently under treatment for referred diagnostic or corrective health problem\046
837~101~4~ST~1~0,0,Referral to another provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment\047scheduled for another appointment with screening provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment for at least one health problem identified during an initial or periodic screening service \040not including dental referrals\041\046
837~101~5,0,Required when a third condition code is necessary\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~101~5,14,Use codes listed in CRC03\046
837~101~5,30,Condition Indicator \0353
837~101~5~AV~1~0,0,Patient refused referral\046
837~101~5~NU~1~0,0,This conditioner indicator must be used when the submitter answers \147N\148 in CRC02\046
837~101~5~S2~1~0,0,Patient is currently under treatment for referred diagnostic or corrective health problem\046
837~101~5~ST~1~0,0,Referral to another provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment\047scheduled for another appointment with screening provider for diagnostic or corrective treatment for at least one health problem identified during an initial or periodic screening service \040not including dental referrals\041\046
