837~162,3,Claim Level Adjustments
837~162,4,Required when the claim has been adjudicated by the payer identified in this loop\044 and the claim has claim level adjustment information\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~162,5,1\046 Submitters must use this CAS segment to report prior payers\146 claim level adjustments that cause the amount paid to differ from the amount originally charged\046\r\n2\046 Only one Group Code is allowed per CAS\046 If it is necessary to send more than one Group Code at the claim level\044 repeat the CAS segment\046\r\n3\046 Codes and associated amounts must come from either paper remittance advice or 835s \040Electronic Remittance Advice\041 received on the claim\046 When the information originates from a paper remittance advice that does not use the standard Claim Adjustment Reason Codes\044 the paper values must be converted to standard Claim Adjustment Reason Codes\046\r\n4\046 A single CAS segment contains six repetitions of the \147adjustment trio\148 composed of adjustment reason code\044 adjustment amount\044 and adjustment quantity\046 These six adjustment trios are used to report up to six adjustments related to a particular Claim Adjustment Group Code \040CAS01\041\046 The first non\045zero adjustment is reported in the first adjustment trio \040CAS02\045CAS04\041\046 If there is a second non\045zero adjustment\044 it is reported in the second adjustment trio \040CAS05\045CAS07\041\044 and so on through the sixth adjustment trio \040CAS17\045CAS19\041\046
