837~170~8~II~1~0,0,Required if the HIPAA Individual Patient Identifier is mandated use\046 If not required\044 use value \145MI\146 instead\046
837~170~8~MI~1~0,0,The code MI is intended to be the subscriber\146s\r\nidentification number as assigned by the payer\046 \040For example\044 Insured\146s ID\044 Subscriber\146s ID\044 Health Insurance Claim Number \040HIC\041\044 etc\046\041\r\nMI is also intended to be used in claims submitted to the Indian Health Service\047Contract Health Services \040IHS\047CHS\041 Fiscal Intermediary for the purpose of reporting the Tribe Residency Code \040Tribe County State\041\046 In the event that a Social Security Number \040SSN\041 is also available on an IHS\047CHS claim\044 put the SSN in REF02\046 When sending the Social Security Number as the Member ID\044 it must be a string of exactly nine numbers with no separators\046 For example\044 sending \147111002222\148 would be valid\044 while sending \147111\04500\0452222\148 would be invalid\046
