837~22,3,Billing Provider Name
837~22,5,1\046 Beginning on the NPI compliance date\058 When the Billing Provider is an organization health care provider\044 the organization health care provider\146s NPI or its subpart\146s NPI is reported in NM109\046 When a health care provider organization has determined that it needs to enumerate its subparts\044 it will report the NPI of a subpart as the Billing Provider\046 The subpart reported as the Billing Provider MUST always represent the most detailed level of enumeration as determined by the organization health care provider and MUST be the same identifier sent to any trading partner\046 For additional explanation\044 see section 1\04610\0463 Organization Health Care Provider Subpart Presentation\046\r\n2\046 Prior to the NPI compliance date\044 proprietary identifiers necessary for the receiver to identify the Billing Provider entity are to be reported in the REF segment of Loop ID\0452010BB\046\r\n3\046 The Taxpayer Identifying Number \040TIN\041 of the Billing Provider to be used for 1099 purposes must be reported in the REF segment of this loop\046\r\n4\046 When the individual or the organization is not a health care provider and\044 thus\044 not eligible to receive an NPI \040For example\044 personal care services\044 carpenters\044 etc\041\044 the Billing Provider should be the legal entity\046 However\044 willing trading partners may agree upon varying definitions\046 Proprietary identifiers necessary for the receiver to identify the entity are to be reported in the Loop ID\0452010BB REF\044 Billing Provider Secondary Identification segment\046 The TIN to be used for 1099 purposes must be reported in the REF \040Tax Identification Number\041 segment of this loop\046
