837~28,5,1\046 When the communication number represents a telephone number in the United States and other countries using the North American Dialing Plan \040for voice\044 data\044 fax\044 etc\046\041\044 the communication number must always include the area code and phone number using the format AAABBBCCCC where AAA is the area code\044 BBB is the telephone number prefix\044 and CCCC is the telephone number\046 Therefore\044 the following telephone number \040555\041 555\0451234 would be represented as 5555551234\046 Do not submit long distance access numbers\044 such as \1471\148\044 in the telephone number\046 Telephone extensions\044 when applicable\044 must be submitted in the next element immediately following the telephone number\046 When submitting telephone extensions\044 only submit the numeric extension\046 Do not include data that indicates an extension\044 such as \147ext\148 or \147x\045\148\046\r\n2\046 There are 2 repetitions of the PER segment to allow for six possible combinations of communication numbers including extensions\046
