837~320,3,Claim information
837~320,5,1\046 The developers of this implementation guide recommend that trading partners limit the size of the transaction \040ST\045SE envelope\041 to a maximum of 5000 CLM segments\046 There is no recommended limit to the number of ST\045SE transactions within a GS\045GE or ISA\045IEA\046 Willing trading partners can agree to set limits higher\046\r\n2\046 For purposes of this documentation\044 the claim detail information is presented only in the patient level\046 Specific claim detail information can be given in either the Subscriber or the Patient hierarchical level\046 Because of this the claim information is said to \147float\046\148 Claim information is positioned in the same hierarchical level that describes its owner\045participant\044 either the Subscriber or the Patient\046 In other words\044 the claim information\044 loop 2300\044 is placed following loop 2010BB in the Subscriber Hierarchical Level \040HL\041 when patient information is sent in loop 2010BA of the Subscriber HL\046 Claim information is placed in the Patient hierarchical level when the patient information is sent in loop 2010CA of the Patient HL\046 When the patient is the subscriber or is considered to be the subscriber\044 loops 2000C and 2010CA are not sent\046 See Subscriber\047Patient HL Segment explanation in section 1\0464\0463\0462\0462\0461 for details\046
837~320,7,CLM\04212345656\042500\042\042\04211\058A\0581\042Y\042A\042Y\042I\126
837~320~1,1,Patient Control Number
837~320~1,14,The number that the submitter transmits in this position is echoed back to the submitter in the 835 and other transactions\046 This permits the submitter to use the value in this field as a key in the submitter\146s system to match the claim to the payment information returned in the 835 transaction\046 The two recommended identifiers are either the Patient Account Number or the Claim Number in the billing submitter\146s patient management system\046 The developers of this implementation guide strongly recommend that submitters use unique numbers for this field for each individual claim\046\r\nWhen Loop ID 2010AC is present\044 CLM01 represents the subrogated Medicaid agency\146s ICN from their original 835 CLP07 \045 Payer Claim Control Number\046 See section 1\0464\0461\0464 of the front matter for a description of post payment recovery claims for subrogated Medicaid agencies\046\r\nThe maximum number of characters to be supported for this field is \14520\146\046 Characters beyond the maximum are not required to be stored nor returned by any 837\045receiving system\046
837~320~11~1,1,Related Causes Code
837~320~2,1,Total Claim Charge Amount
837~320~2,14,The Total Claim Charge Amount must be greater than or equal to zero\046\r\nThe total claim charge amount must balance to the sum of all service line charge amounts reported in the Institutional Service Line \040SV2\041 segments for this claim\046
