837~44~1,14,HL01 must be incremented by one each time an HL is used within each ST\047SE envelope\046 Only numeric values are allowed in HL01\046
837~44~4,14,The claim loop \040Loop ID\0452300\041 can be used when HL04 has no subordinate levels \040HL04 \061 0\041 or when HL04 has subordinate levels indicated \040HL04 \061 1\041\046\r\nIn the first case \040HL04 \061 0\041\044 the subscriber is the patient and there are no dependent claims\046\r\nThe second case \040HL04 \061 1\041 happens when claims for one or more dependents of the subscriber are being sent under the same billing provider HL \040for example\044 a spouse and son are both treated by the same provider\041\046 In that case\044 the subscriber HL04 \061 1 because there is at least one dependent to this subscriber\046 The dependent HL \040spouse\041 would then be sent followed by the 2300 loop for the spouse\046 The next HL would be the dependent HL for the son followed by the 2300 loop for the son\046\r\nIn order to send claims for the subscriber and one or more dependents\044 the Subscriber HL\044 with Relationship Code SBR02\06118 \040Self\041\044 would be followed by the Subscriber\146s 2300 loop for the Subscriber\146s claims\046 Then the Subscriber HL would be repeated\044 followed by one or more Patient HL loops for the dependents\044 with the proper Relationship Code in PAT01\044 each followed by their respective 2300 loop\040s\041 for each dependent\146s claims\046
