837~501~6,0,Required when PWK02 \061 \147BM\148\044 \147EL\148\044 \147EM\148\044 \147FX\148 or \147FT\148\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~501~6,1,Attachment Control Number
837~501~6,14,PWK06 is used to identify the attached electronic documentation\046 The number in PWK06 is carried in the TRN of the electronic attachment\046\r\nFor the purpose of this implementation\044 the maximum field length is 50\046
837~502,0,The CR1 through CR5 and CRC certification segments appear on both the claim level and the service line level because certifications can be submitted for all services on a claim or for individual services\046 Certification information at the claim level applies to all service lines of the claim\044 unless overridden by certification information at the service line level\046
837~508,3,Date \045 Service Date
837~508,4,Required on outpatient service lines where a drug is not being billed and the Statement Covers Period is greater than one day\046\r\nOR\r\nRequired on service lines where a drug is being billed and the payer\146s adjudication is known to be impacted by the drug duration or the date the prescription was written\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~508,5,1\046 In cases where a drug is being billed on a service line\044 date range may be used to indicate drug duration for which the drug supply will be used by the patient\046 The difference in dates\044 including both the begin and end dates\044 are the days supply of the drug\046 Example\058 20000101 \045 20000107 \0401\0471\04700 to 1\0477\04700\041 is used for a 7 day supply where the first day of the drug used by the patient is 1\0471\04700\046 In the event a drug is administered on less than a daily basis \040for example\044 every other day\041 the date range would include the entire period during which the drug was supplied\044 including the last day the drug was used\046 Example\058 20000101 \045 20000108 \0401\0471\04700 to 1\0478\04700\041 is used for an 8 days supply where the prescription is written for Q48 \040every 48 hours\041\044 four doses of the drug are dispensed and the first dose is used on 1\0471\04700\046\r\n2\046 In cases where a drug is being billed on a service line\044 a single date may be used to indicate the date the prescription was written \040or otherwise communicated by the prescriber if not written\041\046
837~508,7,DTP\042472\042D8\04220060108\126
