837~512,3,Line Item Control Number
837~512,4,Required when the submitter needs a line item control number for subsequent communications to or from the payer\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~512,5,1\046 The line item control number must be unique within a patient control number \040CLM01\041\046 Payers are required to return this number in the remittance advice transaction \040835\041 if the provider sends it to them in the 837 and adjudication is based upon line item detail\046\r\n2\046 Submitters are STRONGLY encouraged to routinely send a unique line item control number on all service lines\044 particularly if the submitter automatically posts their remittance advice\046 Submitting a unique line item control number allows the capability to automatically post by service line\046
