837~525,4,Required when dispensing of the drug has been done with an assigned prescription number\046\r\nOR\r\nRequired when the provided medication involves the compounding of two or more drugs being reported and there is no prescription number\046\r\nIf not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~525,5,1\046 In cases where a compound drug is being billed\044 the components of the compound will all have the same prescription number\046 Payers receiving the claim can relate all the components by matching the prescription number\046\r\n2\046 For cases where the drug is provided without a prescription \040for example\044 from a physician\146s office\041\044 the value provided in this segment is a \147link sequence number\148\046 The link sequence number is a provider assigned number that is unique to this claim\046 Its purpose is to enable the receiver to piece together the components of the compound\046
