837~81,5,1\046 Generally\044 preauthorization numbers are assigned by the payer or UMO to authorize a service prior to its being performed\046 The UMO \040Utilization Management Organization\041 is generally the entity empowered to make a decision regarding the outcome of a health services review or the owner of information\046 The prior authorization number carried in this REF is specific to the destination payer reported in the Loop ID\0452010BB\046 If other payers have similar numbers for this claim\044 report that information in the Loop ID\0452330 loop REF which holds that payer\146s information\046\r\n2\046 Numbers at this position apply to the entire claim unless they are overridden in the REF segment in Loop ID\0452400\046 A reference identification is considered to be overridden if the value in REF01 is the same in both the Loop ID\0452300 REF segment and the Loop ID\0452400 REF segment\046 In that case\044 the Loop ID\0452400 REF applies only to that specific line\046
