837~91,4,Required when ALL of the following conditions are met\058\r\n\149 A state concludes it must use the K3 to meet an emergency legislative requirement\059\r\n\149 The administering state agency or other state organization has completed each one of the following steps\058\r\n   contacted the X12N workgroup\044\r\n   requested a review of the K3 data requirement to ensure there is not an existing method within the implementation guide to meet this requirement\r\n\149 X12N determines that there is no method to meet the requirement\046\r\nIf not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
837~91,5,1\046 At the time of publication of this  implementation\044 K3 segments have no specific use\046 The K3 segment is expected to be used only when necessary to meet the unexpected data requirement of a legislative authority\046 Before this segment can be used \058\r\n\045 The X12N Health Care Claim workgroup must conclude there is no other available option in the implementation guide to meet the emergency legislative requirement\046\r\n\045 The requestor must submit a proposal for approval accompanied by the relevant business documentation to the X12N Health Care Claim workgroup chairs and receive approval for the request\046 Upon review of the request\044 X12N will issue an approval or denial decision to the requesting entity\046 Approved usage\040s\041 of the K3 segment will be reviewed by the X12N Health Care Claim workgroup to develop a permanent change to include the business case in future transaction implementations\046\r\n2\046 Only when all of the requirements above have been met\044 may the regulatory agency require the temporary use of the K3 segment\046\r\n3\046 X12N will submit the necessary data maintenance and refer the request to the appropriate data content committee\040s\041\046
837~91,7,K3\042STATE DATA REQUIREMENT\126
