CL1,0,Claim Codes
CL1,1,To supply information specific to hospital claims
CLM,0,Health Claim
CLM,1,To specify basic data about the claim
CLM~0,1,CLM02 is the total amount of all submitted charges of service segments for this claim\046\r\n\r\nCLM06 is provider signature on file indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the provider signature is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the provider signature is not on file\046\r\n\r\nCLM08 is assignment of benefits indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates insured or authorized person authorizes benefits to be assigned to the provider\059 an \034N\034 value indicates benefits have not been assigned to the provider\046\r\n\r\nCLM13 is CHAMPUS nonavailability indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates a statement of non\045availability is on file\059 an \034N\034 value indicates statement of nonavailability is not on file or not necessary\046\r\n\r\nCLM15 is charges itemized by service indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates charges are itemized by service\059 an \034N\034 value indicates charges are summarized by service\046\r\n\r\nCLM18 is explanation of benefit \040EOB\041 indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that a paper EOB is requested\059 an \034N\034 value indicates that no paper EOB is requested\046\r\n\r\n
CN1,0,Contract Information
CN1,1,To specify basic data about the contract or contract line item
CN1,2,Required when the submitter is contractually obligated to supply this information on post\045adjudicated claims\046 If not required by this implementation guide\044 may be provided at the sender\146s discretion\044 but cannot be required by the receiver\046
CN1,3,1\046 The developers of this implementation guide note that the CN1 segment is for use only for post\045adjudicated claims\044 which do not meet the definition of a health care claim under HIPAA\046 Consequently\044 at the time of this writing\044 the CN1 segment will be for non\045HIPAA use only\046
CN1,4,CN1\04202\042550\126
CN1~0,1,CN102 is the contract amount\046\r\n\r\nCN103 is the allowance or charge percent\046\r\n\r\nCN104 is the contract code\046\r\n\r\nCN106 is an additional identifying number for the contract\046\r\n\r\n
CR1,0,Ambulance Certification
CR1,1,To supply information related to the ambulance service rendered to a patient
CR1~0,1,CR102 is the weight of the patient at time of transport\046\r\n\r\nCR106 is the distance traveled during transport\046\r\n\r\nCR107 is the address of origin\046\r\n\r\nCR108 is the address of destination\046\r\n\r\nCR109 is the purpose for the round trip ambulance service\046\r\n\r\nCR110 is the purpose for the usage of a stretcher during ambulance service\046\r\n\r\n
CR2,0,Chiropractic Certification
CR2,1,To supply information related to the chiropractic service rendered to a patient
CR2~0,1,CR201 is the number this treatment is in the series\046\r\n\r\nCR202 is the total number of treatments in the series\046\r\n\r\nCR206 is the time period involved in the treatment series\046\r\n\r\nCR207 is the number of treatments rendered in the month of service\046\r\n\r\nCR209 is complication indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates a complicated condition\059 an \034N\034 value indicates an uncomplicated condition\046\r\n\r\nCR210 is a description of the patient\039s condition\046\r\n\r\nCR211 is an additional description of the patient\039s condition\046\r\n\r\nCR212 is X\045rays availability indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates X\045rays are maintained and available for carrier review\059 an \034N\034 value indicates X\045rays are not maintained and available for carrier review\046\r\n\r\n
CR2~0,2,When both CR203 and CR204 are present\044 CR203 is the beginning level of subluxation and CR204 is the ending level of subluxation\046\r\n\r\n
CR3,0,Durable Medical Equipment Certification
CR3,1,To supply information regarding a physician\039s certification for durable medical equipment
CR3~0,1,CR302 and CR303 specify the time period covered by this certification\046\r\n\r\nCR305 is the prognosis of the patient\046\r\n\r\n
CR4,0,Enteral or Parenteral Therapy Certification
CR4,1,To supply information regarding certification of medical necessity for enteral or parenteral nutrition therapy
CR4~0,1,CR401 is enteral or parenteral indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates enteral\059 an \034N\034 value indicates parenteral\046\r\n\r\nCR404 is the estimated duration of therapy\046\r\n\r\nCR406 is the time period covered by this certification\046\r\n\r\nCR409 is the age of the patient\046\r\n\r\nCR411 is the height of the patient\046\r\n\r\nCR413 is the weight of the patient\046\r\n\r\nCR414 is the number of times the patient is fed per week for parenteral claims or the number of times the patient is fed per day for enteral claims\046\r\n\r\nCR415 is the product name\046\r\n\r\nCR418 is the total number of calories per day of all nutrients prescribed\046\r\n\r\nCR419 is the total number of calories per day prescribed for this product\046\r\n\r\nCR420 is the amino acid name\046\r\n\r\nCR421 is the number of milliliters of amino acid solution used in the prescription per day\046\r\n\r\nCR422 is the percentage of concentration of amino acid used in the prescription\046\r\n\r\nCR423 is the number of grams of amino acid used per day\046\r\n\r\nCR424 is the number of milliliters of dextrose solution used in the prescription per day\046\r\n\r\nCR425 is the percentage of concentration of dextrose used in the prescription\046\r\n\r\nCR426 is the number of milliliters of lipids used in the prescription\046\r\n\r\nCR427 is the percentage of concentration of lipids used in the prescription\046\r\n\r\nCR428 is the number of times per week lipids are used in the prescription\046\r\n\r\nCR429 is the special circumstances or medical justification\046\r\n\r\n
CR5,0,Oxygen Therapy Certification
CR5,1,To supply information regarding certification of medical necessity for home oxygen therapy
CR5~0,1,CR502 is the number of months covered by this certification\046\r\n\r\nCR505 is the reason for equipment\046\r\n\r\nCR506 is the oxygen flow rate in liters per minute\046\r\n\r\nCR507 is the number of times per day the patient must use oxygen\046\r\n\r\nCR508 is the number of hours per period of oxygen use\046\r\n\r\nCR509 is the special orders for the respiratory therapist\046\r\n\r\nCR510 is the arterial blood gas\046\r\n\r\nCR511 is the oxygen saturation\046\r\n\r\nCR516 is the oxygen flow rate for a portable oxygen system in liters per minute\046\r\n\r\n
CR6,0,Home Health Care Certification
CR6,1,To supply information related to the certification of a home health care patient
CR6~0,1,CR602 is the date covered home health services began\046\r\n\r\nCR604 is the certification period covered by this plan of treatment\046\r\n\r\nCR605 is the date of onset or exacerbation of the principal diagnosis\046\r\n\r\nA \034Y\034 value indicates patient is receiving care in a 1861J1 \040skilled nursing\041 facility\046 An \034N\034 value indicates patient is not receiving care in a 1861J1 facility\046 A \034U\034 value indicates it is unknown whether or not the patient is receiving care in a 1861J1 facility\046\r\n\r\nCR607 indicates if the patient is covered by Medicare\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the patient is covered by Medicare\059 an \034N\034 value indicates patient is not covered by Medicare\046\r\n\r\nCR609 is the date that the surgery identified in CR611 was performed\046\r\n\r\nCR610 qualifies CR611\046\r\n\r\nCR611 is the surgical procedure most relevant to the care being rendered\046\r\n\r\nCR612 is the date the agency received the verbal orders from the physician for start of care\046\r\n\r\nCR613 is the date that the patient was last seen by the physician\046\r\n\r\nCR614 is the date of the home health agency\039s most recent contact with the physician\046\r\n\r\nCR616 is the date range of the most recent inpatient stay\046\r\n\r\nCR617 indicates the type of facility from which the patient was most recently discharged\046\r\n\r\nCR618 is the date of onset or exacerbation of the first secondary diagnosis\046\r\n\r\nCR619 is the date of onset or exacerbation of the second secondary diagnosis\046\r\n\r\nCR620 is the date of onset or exacerbation of the third secondary diagnosis\046\r\n\r\nCR621 is the date of onset or exacerbation of the fourth secondary diagnosis\046\r\n\r\n
