HI,1,To supply information related to the delivery of health care
HL,0,Hierarchical Level
HL,1,To identify dependencies among and the content of hierarchically related groups of data segments
HL~0,2,The HL segment is used to identify levels of detail information using a hierarchical structure\044 such as relating line\045item data to shipment data\044 and packaging data to line\045item data\046\r\n\r\nThe HL segment defines a top\045down\047left\045right ordered structure\046\r\n\r\nHL01 shall contain a unique alphanumeric number for each occurrence of the HL segment in the transaction set\046 For example\044 HL01 could be used to indicate the number of occurrences of the HL segment\044 in which case the value of HL01 would be \0341\034 for the initial HL segment and would be incremented by one in each subsequent HL segment within the transaction\046\r\n\r\nHL02 identifies the hierarchical ID number of the HL segment to which the current HL segment is subordinate\046\r\n\r\nHL03 indicates the context of the series of segments following the current HL segment up to the next occurrence of an HL segment in the transaction\046 For example\044 HL03 is used to indicate that subsequent segments in the HL loop form a logical grouping of data referring to shipment\044 order\044 or item\045level information\046\r\n\r\nHL04 indicates whether or not there are subordinate \040or child\041 HL segments related to the current HL segment\046\r\n\r\n
