NTE~0,2,The NTE segment permits free\045form information\047data which\044 under ANSI X12 standard implementations\044 is not machine processible\046 The use of the NTE segment should therefore be avoided\044 if at all possible\044 in an automated environment\046\r\n\r\n
OI,0,Other Health Insurance Information
OI,1,To specify information associated with other health insurance coverage
OI~0,1,OI03 is the assignment of benefits indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates insured or authorized person authorizes benefits to be assigned to the provider\059 an \034N\034 value indicates benefits have not been assigned to the provider\046\r\n\r\n
PAT,0,Patient Information
PAT,1,To supply patient information
PAT~0,1,PAT06 is the date of death\046\r\n\r\nPAT08 is the patient\039s weight\046\r\n\r\nPAT09 indicates whether the patient is pregnant or not pregnant\046  Code \034Y\034 indicates the patient is pregnant\059 code \034N\034 indicates the patient is not pregnant\046\r\n\r\n
PER,0,Administrative Communications Contact
PER,1,To identify a person or office to whom administrative communications should be directed
PRV,0,Provider Information
PRV,1,To specify the identifying characteristics of a provider
PS1,0,Purchase Service
PS1,1,To specify the information about services that are purchased
PS1~0,1,PS101 is provider identification number\046\r\n\r\nPS102 is cost of the purchased service\046\r\n\r\nPS103 is the state where the service is purchased\046\r\n\r\n
PWK,0,Paperwork
PWK,1,To identify the type or transmission or both of paperwork or supporting information
PWK~0,2,PWK05 and PWK06 may be used to identify the addressee by a code number\046\r\n\r\nPWK07 may be used to indicate special information to be shown on the specified report\046\r\n\r\nPWK08 may be used to indicate action pertaining to a report\046\r\n\r\n
QTY,0,Quantity Information
QTY,1,To specify quantity information
QTY~0,1,QTY04 is used when the quantity is non\045numeric\046\r\n\r\n
REF,0,Reference Information
REF,1,To specify identifying information
REF~0,1,REF04 contains data relating to the value cited in REF02\046\r\n\r\n
SBR,0,Subscriber Information
SBR,1,To record information specific to the primary insured and the insurance carrier for that insured
SBR~0,1,SBR02 specifies the relationship to the person insured\046\r\n\r\nSBR03 is policy or group number\046\r\n\r\nSBR04 is plan name\046\r\n\r\nSBR07 is destination payer code\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates the payer is the destination payer\059 an \034N\034 value indicates the payer is not the destination payer\046\r\n\r\n
SE,0,Transaction Set Trailer
SE,1,To indicate the end of the transaction set and provide the count of the transmitted segments \040including the beginning \040ST\041 and ending \040SE\041 segments\041
SE~0,2,SE is the last segment of each transaction set\046\r\n\r\n
ST,0,Transaction Set Header
ST,1,To indicate the start of a transaction set and to assign a control number
ST,3,ST\042837\042987654\042005010X223\126
ST~0,1,The transaction set identifier \040ST01\041 is used by the translation routines of the interchange partners to select the appropriate transaction set definition \040e\046g\046\044 810 selects the Invoice Transaction Set\041\046\r\n\r\nThe implementation convention reference \040ST03\041 is used by the translation routines of the interchange partners to select the appropriate implementation convention to match the transaction set definition\046  When used\044 this implementation convention reference takes precedence over the implementation reference specified in the GS08\046\r\n\r\n
SV1,0,Professional Service
SV1,1,To specify the service line item detail for a health care professional
SV1~0,1,SV102 is the submitted service line item amount\046\r\n\r\nSV105 is the place of service\046\r\n\r\nSV108 is the independent lab charges\046\r\n\r\nSV109 is the emergency\045related indicator\059 a \034Y\034 value indicates service provided was emergency related\059 an \034N\034 value indicates service provided was not emergency related\046\r\n\r\nSV111 is early and periodic screen for diagnosis and treatment of children \040EPSDT\041 involvement\059 a \034Y\034 value indicates EPSDT involvement\059 an \034N\034 value indicates no EPSDT involvement\046\r\n\r\nSV112 is the family planning involvement indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates family planning services involvement\059 an \034N\034 value indicates no family planning services involvement\046\r\n\r\nSV117 is the health care manpower shortage area \040HMSA\041 facility identification\046\r\n\r\nSV118 is the health care manpower shortage area \040HMSA\041 zip code\046\r\n\r\nSV119 is a non\045covered service amount\046\r\n\r\n
SV1~0,2,If SV113 is equal to \034L\034 or \034N\034\044 then SV114 is required\046\r\n\r\n
SV2,0,Institutional Service
SV2,1,To specify the service line item detail for a health care institution
SV2~0,1,SV201 is the revenue code\046\r\n\r\nSV203 is the submitted service line item amount\046\r\n\r\nSV207 is a non\045covered service amount\046\r\n\r\nSV208 is the detail service line indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates a detail service line\059 an \034N\034 value indicates a summary service line\046\r\n\r\n
SV3,0,Dental Service
SV3,1,To specify the service line item detail for dental work
SV3~0,1,SV302 is the submitted service line item amount\046\r\n\r\nSV303 is the place of service code representing the location where the dental treatment was rendered\046\r\n\r\nSV306 is the number of procedures\046\r\n\r\nSV307 is the reason for replacement\046\r\n\r\nSV310 is the predetermination of benefits indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that this service is being submitted for predetermination of benefits\046\r\n\r\n
SV4,0,Drug Service
SV4,1,To specify the claim service detail for prescription drugs
SV4~0,1,SV401 is a prescription number\046\r\n\r\nSV403 is a new or refill number\046 A value of zero indicates a new prescription\044 any other value is the refill number of an existing prescription\046\r\n\r\nSV404 is the generic indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates a generic drug\059 an \034N\034 value indicates a branded drug\046\r\n\r\nSV408 is the drug name\046\r\n\r\nSV409 is the multisource indicator\046 A \034Y\034 indicates drug is available from more than one manufacturer\059 an \034N\034 value indicates drug is available from one manufacturer\046\r\n\r\nSV410 is the compound indicator\046 A \034Y\034 indicates a compound drug\059 an \034N\034 value indicates a noncompound drug\046 A \034U\034 value indicates a nonspecified drug compound\046\r\n\r\n
SV5,0,Durable Medical Equipment Service
SV5,1,To specify the claim service detail for durable medical equipment
SV5~0,1,SV503 is the length of medical treatment required\046\r\n\r\nSV504 is the rental price\046\r\n\r\nSV505 is the purchase price\046\r\n\r\nSV506 is the frequency at which the rental equipment is billed\046\r\n\r\n
SV6,0,Anesthesia Service
SV6,1,To specify the claim service detail for anesthesia
SV6~0,1,SV604 is the submitted charge\046\r\n\r\nSV606 is the number of anesthesia minutes\046\r\n\r\nSV607 is the Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist \040CRNA\041 supervision indicator\046 A \034Y\034 value indicates that services were performed personally by a CRNA who was medically directed by a physician other than the operating surgeon\044 assistant surgeon\044 or attending physician\059 an \034N\034 value indicates that the services were performed personally by a CRNA who was medically directed by the operating surgeon\044 assistant surgeon\044 or attending physician\046\r\n\r\n
SV7,0,Drug Adjudication
SV7,1,To specify the claim service detail for drug services that have been adjudicated
SV7~0,1,SV701 is an internal processing identification number\046\r\n\r\nSV702 is the number assigned to the doctor who wrote the prescription\046\r\n\r\nThis code is used to indicate or verify the patient\039s benefit coverage level at the time the claim was adjudicated\046\r\n\r\nSV705 describes the legal status \040characteristic\041 of the drug being dispensed\046\r\n\r\nSV706 is the Drug Utilization Review \040DUR\041 alert indicator\046 A \034Y\034 indicates a DUR alert was issued\059 an \034N\034 indicates DUR processing occurred but no alert was issued\046\r\n\r\n
SVD,0,Service Line Adjudication
SVD,1,To convey service line adjudication information for coordination of benefits between the initial payers of a health care claim and all subsequent payers
SVD~0,1,SVD01 is the payer identification code\046\r\n\r\nSVD02 is the amount paid for this service line\046\r\n\r\nSVD04 is the revenue code\046\r\n\r\nSVD05 is the paid units of service\046\r\n\r\n
SVD~0,2,SVD03 represents the medical procedure code upon which adjudication of this service line was based\046 This may be different than the submitted medical procedure code\046\r\n\r\nSVD06 is only used for bundling of service lines\046 It references the LX Assigned Number of the service line into which this service line was bundled\046\r\n\r\n
TOO,0,Tooth Identification
TOO,1,To identify a tooth by number and\044 if applicable\044 one or more tooth surfaces
UR,0,Peer Review Organization or Utilization Review
UR,1,To specify the results of the utilization review
UR~0,1,UR02 is the number of grace days\046\r\n\r\n
