1028,3,Patient Control Number
1028,14,The number that the submitter transmits in this position is echoed back to the submitter in the 835 and other transactions\046 This permits the submitter to use the value in this field as a key in the submitter\146s system to match the claim to the payment information returned in the 835 transaction\046 The two recommended identifiers are either the Patient Account Number or the Claim Number in the billing submitter\146s patient management system\046 The developers of this implementation guide strongly recommend that submitters use unique numbers for this field for each individual claim\046\r\nWhen Loop ID 2010AC is present\044 CLM01 represents the subrogated Medicaid agency\146s ICN from their original 835 CLP07 \045 Payer Claim Control Number\046 See section 1\0464\0461\0464 of the front matter for a description of post payment recovery claims for subrogated Medicaid agencies\046\r\nThe maximum number of characters to be supported for this field is \14520\146\046 Characters beyond the maximum are not required to be stored nor returned by any 837\045receiving system\046
