66,0,Identification Code Qualifier
66,1,Code designating the system\047method of code structure used for Identification Code \04067\041 
66,2,Required for providers in the United States or its territories on or after the mandated National Provider Identifier \040NPI\041 implementation date when the provider is eligible to receive an NPI\046\r\nOR\r\nRequired for providers in the United States or its territories before the mandated NPI implementation date when the provider has received an NPI and the submitter has the capability to send it\046\r\nOR\r\nRequired for providers not in the United States or its territories when the provider has received an NPI\046\r\nIf not required by this implementation guide\044 do not send\046
66,14,On or after the mandated implementation date for the HIPAA National Plan Identifier \040National Plan ID\041\044 XV must be sent\046\r\nPrior to the mandated implementation date and prior to any phasein period identified by Federal regulation\044 PI must be sent\046\r\nIf a phase\045in period is designated\044 PI must be sent unless\058\r\n1\046 Both the sender and receiver agree to use the National Plan ID\044\r\n2\046 The receiver has a National Plan ID\044 and\r\n3\046 The sender has the capability to send the National Plan ID\046\r\nIf all of the above conditions are true\044 XV must be sent\046 In this case the Payer Identification Number that would have been sent using qualifier PI can be sent in the corresponding REF segment using qualifier 2U\046
